<HEADLINE>
<P>
EARTHQUAKE: THE LONG ROAD BACK; FEELING THE AFTERSHOCKS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Researched by APRIL JACKSON / Los Angeles Times 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 This chart shows Monday's 6.6 earthquake compared to all the aftershocks, 3.0 
magnitude and greater, from 4:30 a.m. Monday till 6:19 a.m. Thursday. A 
magnitude increase of one full point is equal to a tenfold increase in a 
quake's power.The difference between the quake and the aftershocks is much 
greater than shown here. The scale has been adjusted in order to make the bars 
for the aftershocks visible. 
</P>
