<HEADLINE>
<P>
FOR SALE IN BRITAIN: BUNKER WITH A VIEW 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Reuters 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 With the Cold War over, Britain's Defense Ministry has put 21 underground 
bunkers up for sale, euphemistically calling them "small country estates with a 
view." 
</P>
<P>
 The bunkers, measuring 15 by 3 1/2 feet, were constructed to be manned by 
soldiers in the event of nuclear war. 
</P>
<P>
 Ministry officials say the bunkers could make ideal wine cellars, bases for 
camping or even ultra-quiet country retreats. 
</P>
<P>
 Many are situated in areas of natural beauty with lovely views, they said. 
</P>
