<HEADLINE>
<P>
NATION IN BRIEF; NATIONWIDE; WOMEN TOP MEN IN THEIR ASPIRATIONS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Staff and Wire Reports 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 A record number of women intend to become doctors or lawyers or enter other 
professions that require advanced college degrees, according to a major annual 
survey of college freshmen that shows women's aspirations are higher than 
men's. More than 66% of female college freshmen plan to earn advanced degrees, 
compared with 63% of males. More women also plan to pursue medical, law or 
doctoral degrees -- a record 27.3% of female freshmen, compared with 25.8% of 
males, according to the survey by the UCLA Higher Education Research Institute. 
</P>
