<HEADLINE>
<P>
GOLF ROUNDUP; MAGEE WINS FIRST CHAMPIONSHIP SINCE 1991 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Associated Press 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Andrew Magee's errorless final round of 67 on the par-72 Tucson National 
course kept him ahead of all challengers and produced a two-shot victory Sunday 
at the Northern Telecom Open. 
</P>
<P>
 Magee, 31, started his 10th PGA Tour season with his first title since 1991 
and fourth overall.His four-day total was 18-under 270. He won $198,000. 
</P>
<P>
 Jay Don Blake, Loren Roberts, Vijay Singh and Steve Stricker tied at 272. 
Roberts shot a 64, the day's lowest round, and Singh carded a 65. 
</P>
<P>
 Magee birdied Nos. 3, 8, 11 and 14, then finished with four consecutive pars 
while Blake and Stricker, his closest pursuers, faltered. 
</P>
<P>
 Olin Browne had the shot of the day on the 495-yard, par-five No. 2 when he 
made double eagle-two by sinking a four-iron shot from 217 yards away. 
</P>
<P>
 But Browne was only two-under for the rest of the round and finished sixth at 
273. 
</P>
<P>
 * 
</P>
<P>
 Patrick Burke of Los Angeles earned his first professional victory, shooting a 
final-round 72 to win the Players' Championship at Melbourne, Australia. 
</P>
<P>
 Burke, who made $100,000 last year, earned $37,800 for the win. 
</P>
<P>
 * 
</P>
<P>
 Leslie Shannon defeated Vicki Thomas, 3 and 1, to win the Ione D. 
Jones-Doherty Women's Match-Play Championship at Ft. Lauderdale, Fla. 
</P>
</TEXT>
