<P>
WEST VENTURA COUNTY FOCUS: CAMARILLO; HOSPITAL FOUNDATION CHAIRWOMAN NAMED 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By J. E. MITCHELL 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Willaine Conroy of Camarillo has been named chairwoman of the board of 
directors of St. John's Pleasant Valley Hospital Foundation, officials said. 
</P>
<P>
 Conroy, 49, succeeds C. Douglas Off as foundation leader.As chairwoman of the 
board, Conroy said she will concentrate on generating community support for the 
Camarillo-based hospital, which last year was merged with St. John's Regional 
Medical Center in Oxnard. 
</P>
<P>
 "We want to get the word out that we are here to serve and help the community 
by working to strengthen local health care," said Conroy, who was installed 
Jan. 11. "Now that we are in a stable position and on the upswing, I am 
confident that we will be able to re-establish strong community rapport (for 
the hospital)." 
</P>
<P>
 A member of the foundation's board of directors since 1991, Conroy added that 
she will also focus on increasing Pleasant Valley's hospital endowment fund. J. 
E. MITCHELL 
</P>
