EAST VENTURA COUNTY FOCUS: MOORPARK; HIGHER TIERRA REJADA SPEED LIMIT OKD 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By JAMES MAIELLA JR. 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The Moorpark City Council has decided to raise the speed limit on Tierra 
Rejada Road from 40 m.p.h. to 45 m.p.h. between Spring Road and the Moorpark 
Freeway, given recent improvements and expansion of the road. 
</P>
<P>
 The council voted 4 to 0 last week to increase the speed on the road, which 
was recently converted from an aging, two-lane stretch to a newly paved, 
four-lane divided highway. 
</P>
<P>
 "With the new and improved road service and an expanded number of lanes, 
people can safely travel faster on that road," Councilman Scott Montgomery 
said. 
</P>
<P>
 Concerned by the road's former condition, council members voted about two 
years ago to reduce the speed from 45 m.p.h. to 40 m.p.h. JAMES MAIELLA JR. 
</P>
</TEXT>
