<P>
WEST VENTURA COUNTY FOCUS: CAMARILLO; INFORMATION SOUGHT IN FINDING MAN, 74 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By FRED ALVAREZ 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Sheriff's deputies are asking for the public's help in finding a 74-year-old 
Camarillo man who has been missing since Friday. 
</P>
<P>
 Sam Corsetti was last seen when he left his Camarillo home about 3:30 p.m. 
Friday to get gasoline. He is in need of medical attention and is at times 
forgetful and could be disoriented, authorities said. 
</P>
<P>
 Corsetti was driving a blue Mazda pickup, license number 3N27419. He is 5 
feet, 7 inches tall and weighs 170 pounds, with gray hair and brown eyes. He 
was last seen wearing a plaid green shirt and gray pants. 
</P>
<P>
