<P>
UCLA A NEAR-UNANIMOUS NO. 1 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Times Wire Services 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 UCLA, the nation's only unbeaten Division I team, ascended to the top ranking 
in the USA Today/CNN college basketball coaches' poll released Sunday. 
</P>
<P>
 The Associated Press poll will be out today. 
</P>
<P>
 The Bruins (13-0) are the nation's top-ranked team for the first time since 
January of 1983, when Larry Farmer was the coach. 
</P>
<P>
 Last week, UCLA was tied with Kansas for the No. 1 spot in the USA Today/CNN 
poll and ranked No. 2 behind Kansas in the AP poll. The Jayhawks (17-2) lost to 
Kansas State on Monday. 
</P>
<P>
 The Bruins defeated No. 9-ranked Arizona Thursday night and Arizona State 
Saturday. UCLA was a near-unanimous selection for the top spot in the USA 
Today/CNN poll, receiving 33 of 34 first-place votes and 849 points from the 
coaches' panel. No. 2 Duke (13-1) got the other first-place voice. 
</P>
<P>
 Kansas dropped to No. 3, and Arizona to No. 11. 
</P>
