<HEADLINE>
<P>
ORANGE COUNTY FOCUS: SANTA ANA; NEW COLLEGE TRUSTEE TO BE SELECTED TODAY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By JON NALICK 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The Rancho Santiago Community College District board is expected to select a 
new trustee today from a field of 15 applicants. The Board of Trustees will 
replace Carol Enos, 54, who resigned last month, citing health problems and a 
planned early retirement from her teaching job. 
</P>
<P>
 Applicants include: Richard E. Adams, 47, of Orange; Donald Attore, 43, of 
Orange; Vincent D. De Vargas, 50, of Orange; Dennis J. Donohue, 47, of Orange; 
Euiwon Chough, 63, of Anaheim Hills; Dennis K. Hasty, 54, of Villa Park; Kim F. 
Kadletz, 46, of Orange; Lawrence R. Labrado, 54, of Orange; Nancy E. Manning of 
Orange; Mel Ross, 66, of Orange; Fred Smoller, 39, of Orange; Elizabeth Ann 
Test, 54, of Orange; Ricardo M. Ulivi, 44, of Santa Ana; James D. Vanderbilt, 
28, of Anaheim, and Phillip E. Yarbrough, 33, of Santa Ana.JON NALICK 
</P>
</TEXT>
